Gunmen suspected to be bandits have reportedly invaded a church in Chukun Local Government Area of Kaduna State, killing an unspecified number of worshippers. DAILY POST gathered that the incident occurred on Sunday morning. Details of the incident was still sketchy as at press time. When contacted by DAILY POST correspondent to ascertain the name of the church and confirm the incident, the state’s Police Public Relations Officer, ASP Mohammed Jalige said, “I will find out and get back to you”.